FBIS3-52897 "drnes006_s_94007" FBIS-NES-94-006 Document Type:Daily Report 10 Jan 1994 Iran Ministry Calls For Extended Afghan Cease-Fire LD0801171794 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran First Program Network in Persian 1630 GMT 8 Jan 94 LD0801171794 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran First Program Network Language: Persian Article Type:BFN [Text] The Foreign Ministry of the Islamic Republic of Iran has sent messages to the political and Jehadi leaders of Afghanistan, calling for an extension of the cease-fire. The cease-fire between the warring sides in Afghanistan came into effect at 0600 this morning in response to a request from the Islamic Republic of Iran. The Islamic Republic of Iran has also called for the continuation of negotiations between the engaged parties toward ending the fighting.
